  "market_context": "ETH 5-minute chart showing prior expansion lower followed by a retracement higher into a fair value gap. The setup forms without taking out highs, presenting a continuation opportunity within the higher time frame wick formation rather than an ideal structural setup.",
  "key_observation": "Price expands away, retraces into a fair value gap, and is bought right back up with a closure over the down-close candles — a continuation signature that can be traded even when structure is not ideal, provided HTF wick context is respected.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identify the expansion away followed by a retracement into the fair value gap on the 5-minute chart.",
    "Step 2: Wait for the closure through the opposing down-close candles to confirm the continuation entry.",
    "Step 3: Enter on the closure, place stop on the low of the setup, and target 2R.",
    "Step 4: Acknowledge this is not ideal structure — frame it as an advanced trade based on the higher time frame wick forming.",
    "Step 5: Manage the trade through a near stop-out before price ultimately expands to the target."
  ],
  "outcome": "Trade nearly stopped out but ultimately reached target — profitable 2R outcome.",
  "lessons": "Frame continuation entries while the higher time frame wick is forming. Even non-ideal LTF structure can be traded if the HTF context supports a wick formation, but expect to sit through deeper retracements before expansion.",
